									Huber</persname> in Manuscripts, British Library, on <date normal="20061007" era="ce" calendar="gregorian">07/10/2006</date>.</p>
                     </note>
                  </did>
                  <bibliography>
                     <bibref title="http://www.thomasgray.org/resources/biblb.shtml#SmM_1989"
                             linktype="simple">Smith (ed.), <title render="italic" linktype="simple">Index</title> (1989), item GrT 47,  83</bibref>
                     <bibref title="http://www.thomasgray.org/resources/biblb.shtml#SuD_1995"
                             linktype="simple">Sutton (ed.), <title render="italic" linktype="simple">Location Register</title> (1995),  414</bibref>
                  </bibliography>
                  <scopecontent>
                     <p>Transcript of ll. 1-2 and 5-6 in the hand of <extref href="http://spenserians.cath.vt.edu/authorrecord.php?action=GET&amp;recordid=33384"
                                show="new"
                                linktype="simple">
                           <persname role="trc" normal="Mitford, John, 1781-1859">John
								Mitford</persname>
                        </extref>, here entitled <title render="doublequote" linktype="simple">Epitaph on
									Sir W. Williams.</title> and annotated "Mr. Montague asked him to
								write the Epitaph on Sir W. Williams and he could not refuse. He did not
								know much of him...", in <persname role="trc" normal="Mitford,           John, 1781-1859">John Mitford</persname>, <title render="italic" linktype="simple">Note-Books</title>,	vol. III "Mitford. 
								Extracts from Mr Grays Common-place books", f. 181r.
							</p>
